last_episode_to_air.overview: Dr. Migleemo cooks up some hot dishes while Mariner prefers hers served cold.

name: Star Trek: Lower Decks
overview: The lives of the support crew serving on one of Starfleet's least important ships, the U.S.S. Cerritos, in 2380. Ensigns Mariner, Boimler, Rutherford and Tendi have to keep up with their duties and their social lives, often while the ship is being rocked by a multitude of sci-fi anomalies.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Season three challenges the U.S.S. Cerritos ensigns in (hilarious) ways they could never imagine, starting with a shocking resolution for season two’s epic cliffhanger finale.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: In season five, the crew of the U.S.S. Cerritos is tasked with closing "space potholes" – subspace rifts that are causing chaos in the Alpha Quadrant. Pothole duty would be easy for Junior Officers Mariner, Boimler, Tendi and Rutherford ... If they didn't also have to deal with an Orion war, furious Klingons, diplomatic catastrophes, murder mysteries and scariest of all: their own career aspirations.

tagline: The adventure begins when their shift ends.

episodes.name: Second Contact
episodes.overview: Ensign Tendi has her first day of work on Starfleet's USS Cerritos, where she meets fellow support crew members. Boimler is tasked with a secret special assignment. Rutherford attempts to keep his dating life intact while a disaster strikes the ship.

episodes.name: Envoys
episodes.overview: Ensigns Boimler and Mariner embark on a shuttle mission to a Klingon compound while Ensigns Tendi and Rutherford spend time together back on the USS Cerritos.

episodes.name: Temporal Edict
episodes.overview: A new work protocol eliminating "buffer time" has the Lower Decks crew running ragged as they try to keep up with their tightened schedules. Ensign Mariner and Commander Ransom's mutual lack of respect comes to a head during an away mission.

episodes.name: Moist Vessel
episodes.overview: Captain Freeman seeks the ultimate payback after Mariner blatantly disrespects her in front of the crew. A well-meaning Tendi accidentally messes up a Lieutenant's attempt at spiritual ascension and tries to make it right.

episodes.name: Cupid's Errant Arrow
episodes.overview: Ensign Boimler welcomes his girlfriend Barb onto the USS Cerritos, much to Ensign Mariner’s dismay — while Ensigns Ruthford and Tendi have starship envy when the Cerritos rendezvous with the more-advanced USS Vancouver.

episodes.name: Terminal Provocations
episodes.overview: The lovable but awkward Ensign Fletcher makes work difficult for Mariner and Boimler. Rutherford introduces Tendi to a holodeck training program he created.

episodes.name: Much Ado About Boimler
episodes.overview: Mariner tries to impress her best friend from Starfleet Academy who is now a visiting Captain. Boimler is sent to a Starfleet medical ship after a transporter accident puts him “out of phase.”

episodes.name: Veritas
episodes.overview: Mariner, Boimler, Tendi and Rutherford are caught off guard when aliens force them to testify about a series of seemingly unrelated events.

guest_stars.character: Black Ops Officer 2 / Romulan Guard 1 / Tweerk Captain (voice)
guest_stars.name: Kenneth Mitchell

episodes.name: Crisis Point
episodes.overview: Mariner repurposes Boimler's holodeck program to cast herself as the villain in a Lower Decks style movie.

episodes.name: No Small Parts
episodes.overview: The USS Cerritos encounters a familiar enemy. Tendi helps a struggling recruit find her footing.

episodes.name: Strange Energies
episodes.overview: Approximately three months after the events of the season one finale, the U.S.S. Cerritos is dispatched on a mission where it ends up in a sci-fi event resulting in "strange energy," which Commander Ransom inadvertently absorbs.

episodes.name: Kayshon, His Eyes Open
episodes.overview: Our Lower Deckers have trouble bonding with Ensign Jet Manhaver, who has been assigned Boimler’s bunk and shift duties. Meanwhile, we get a glimpse of Boimler’s life on the U.S.S. Titan, which is more intense than he thought it would be.

guest_stars.character: Ensign Barnes / Gelrakian #1 / U.S.S. Cerritos Computer (voice)
guest_stars.name: Jessica McKenna

episodes.name: We'll Always Have Tom Paris
episodes.overview: Assigned a special task by Dr. T'Ana, Tendi enlists Mariner for help. On the U.S.S. Cerritos, Rutherford is consumed by a bridge crew mystery.

episodes.name: Mugato, Gumato
episodes.overview: The U.S.S. Cerritos is dispatched to a planet to investigate an unexplained sighting of a dangerous Mugato.

episodes.name: An Embarrassment of Dooplers
episodes.overview: Mariner and Boimler try to track down the location of a legendary Starfleet party while the bridge crew deals with an insecure alien diplomat.

episodes.name: The Spy Humongous
episodes.overview: Anomaly consolidation day on the U.S.S. Cerritos leaves the Lower Deckers with mixed emotions. Captain Freeman attempts to negotiate peace on the Pakled home world.

guest_stars.character: Queen Pakled / Out-of-Breath Pakled / Pakled Delegate 2 (voice)
guest_stars.name: Brian Posehn

episodes.name: Where Pleasant Fountains Lie
episodes.overview: Mariner and Boimler are stranded on an uninhabited planet with a sentient computer. On the Cerritos, Lt. Commander Billups must prove his engineering abilities to an old adversary.

episodes.name: I, Excretus
episodes.overview: A consultant arrives on the U.S.S. Cerritos to run drills that require the lower deckers and bridge crew to swap duties.

guest_stars.character: Commanding Officer / Borg Member / Docking Bay Officer (voice)
guest_stars.name: Phil LaMarr

episodes.name: wej Duj
episodes.overview: Boimler tries to find a friend from the bridge, while the crew of the USS Cerritos has free time during a long warp trip.

episodes.name: First First Contact
episodes.overview: In the season two finale, the U.S.S. Cerritos is tasked to aid another class starship on a first contact mission.

episodes.name: Grounded
episodes.overview: Mariner enlists her friends on a rogue mission to exonerate her mother, as Captain Freeman faces a military tribunal for the destruction of Pakled Planet.

episodes.name: The Least Dangerous Game
episodes.overview: On a tropical paradise planet, Mariner questions Commander Ransom on how he structures his away team. Boimler makes a bold career decision.

episodes.name: Mining the Mind's Mines
episodes.overview: On a remote science outpost, stone orbs are bringing fantasies to life. Tendi starts her first day as a Senior Science Officer Trainee.

episodes.name: Room for Growth
episodes.overview: Mariner, Boimler and Tendi clash with their arch-rivals: Delta Shift. The Cerritos engineers go on mandatory relaxation leave.

episodes.name: Reflections
episodes.overview: Mariner and Boimler work the Starfleet recruitment booth at an alien job fair, Rutherford challenges himself.

episodes.name: Hear All, Trust Nothing
episodes.overview: The Cerritos crew unexpectedly spends a day on Deep Space Nine.

episodes.name: A Mathematically Perfect Redemption
episodes.overview: A wayward Starfleet ensign struggles to find a path to redemption.

episodes.name: Crisis Point 2: Paradoxus
episodes.overview: Boimler's holodeck movie sequel tries to live up to the original.

episodes.name: Trusted Sources
episodes.overview: A visiting reporter on the Cerritos puts Captain Freeman on edge.

episodes.name: The Stars at Night
episodes.overview: The Cerritos crew must prove their worth in a mission race.

episodes.name: Twovix
episodes.overview: The Cerritos ensigns must assist a caretaker on the voyage of a historically significant starship.

episodes.name: I Have No Bones Yet I Must Flee
episodes.overview: Mariner tries to get demoted, Rutherford tries to get promoted, and Boimler makes a big move.

episodes.name: In the Cradle of Vexilon
episodes.overview: Boimler leads his first away mission on an alien megastructure.

episodes.name: Something Borrowed, Something Green
episodes.overview: Tendi is summoned back to Orion for a wedding.

episodes.name: Empathalogical Fallacies
episodes.overview: A trio of Betazoids cause chaos on the Cerritos.

episodes.name: Parth Ferengi's Heart Place
episodes.overview: The Cerritos visits the Ferengi homeworld.

episodes.name: A Few Badgeys More
episodes.overview: Three computerized villains return to cause problems for the Cerritos crew.

episodes.name: Caves
episodes.overview: The Lower Deckers go on a classic cave mission.

episodes.name: The Inner Fight (1)
episodes.overview: Captain Freeman assigns the Lower Deckers an overly safe mission to try and keep a self-destructive Mariner out of danger.

episodes.name: Old Friends, New Planets (2)
episodes.overview: Mariner faces her past.

episodes.name: Dos Cerritos
episodes.overview: A spatial anomaly forces the Cerritos crew to face their own faces. Tendi pirates.

episodes.name: Shades of Green
episodes.overview: Tendi races to stop a conflict while Boimler & Mariner race to stop capitalists.

episodes.name: The Best Exotic Nanite Hotel
episodes.overview: The Lower Deckers hunt nanites on a resort...in space?!
